metadata.name: The Cross #12
metadata.description:
The Cross.
The project consists of different layers ( PNG ).

Layers:
-painted background
-painted flower background
-painted stone texture
-painted splashes color
-frames 
-various cross fractals that were randomly generated before

Everything is merged from over 170 png layers.
It is possible to get only a flower background. 
The project was created with the pure spider template.

metadata.name: 3 ways to rome #5
metadata.description:
With this project I have connected my 3 passions.
Analog photography, travel and underwater photography. 
The project is structured in 6 layers ( PNG Layer ). 
All analog images are self-developed and scanned. 
I divided the project into the layers ( dark,bluegreen,brown,grey,texture and frame). All levels are mixed and superimposed. 
I hope you like it.

Generated with the PureSpider Template

metadata.name: We Are Alone Together #346
metadata.description:
We meander through the flows of life, alone but together. This experience — an ultimately solitary one — is communicated but never truly shared. Our consciousnesses live in a perpetual separated state, alone but together.

############

Display resolution scales with window size. Press ’h’ (in live mode) to generate a 6000x7500 hi-res image. This may take a few seconds to generate depending on your hardware. Press ‘d’ to redraw the artwork.

Original artwork by perkwerk * made with p5.js * 2022

metadata.name: dg5721() #56
metadata.description:
A tiny neural network with 5721 neurons, that tries to imitate human handwriting by generating new hallucinated digits in real-time.

It can generate these digits at any resolution and will invent its own ways to fill the gaps.

- Press <SPACE> or click to toggle the infinite latent space exploration.
- Press <S> to save the current frame as PNG at the current screen resolution x2.

It can be installed to work offline (Install button in the URL bar in Chrome or "Add to Home screen" on iOS)

As of 2021, this artwork requires a fast computer or mobile phone.

metadata.name: Skravert #219
metadata.description:
‘Skravert’ - Norwegian, verb, past tense. ‘The act of filling an area with lines; to shade an area’.

Skravert is a series of 320 sketches, each capturing the texture and feel of a material residing somewhere between cardboard and woolen rugs. The project is centred around rectangle subdivision and a line drawing algorithm, giving each piece its own unique expression when combined with a selection of 28 different color  palettes.  

Original artwork by perkwerk * made with p5.js * 2021

metadata.name: sinuosity #54
metadata.description:
sinuosity is defined as:

- (n.) the ability to curve or bend easily and flexibly.

sinuous is defined as a couple of things:

- (adj.) having many curves and turns.
- (adj.) lithe and supple.

each curve anchors to the center. 

maybe that center is a life. (maybe that center is you.)

maybe that curve is a relationship. (or a job.) (or repressed trauma that needs processing.)

maybe that curve has other curves within. (it probably does.)

sometimes there are many curves at once. (usually this the case.) 

occasionally, there may only be one. (life isn’t always so complicated.) 

whatever curves the moment contains it can help to step away and see how they come together. (this is not always easy.)
